MOST IMMEDIATE
No.55/1/1/84-Cab.
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA (BHARAT SARKAR)
CABINET SECRETARIAT (MANTRIMANDAL SACHIVALAYA)
New Delhi, the 19th July, 1984.
28th Asadha, 1906 (S)
The undersigned is directed to state that with
effect from the 19th July, 1984,
Smt. Indira Gandhi, Prime Minister assumed
also the Office of the Minister of External
Affairs;
(i)
Shri P.C. Sethi relinquished the Office
of the Minister of Home Affairs and assumed
the Office of the Minister of Planning;
(ii)
(iii) Shri P.V. Narasimha Rao relinquished the
Office of the Minister of External Affairs
and assumed the Office of the Minister
of Home Affairs; and
(iv) Shri S.B. Chavan relinquished the Office of
the Minister of Planning and assumed the
Office of the Minister Without Portfolio. He
will also assist the Prime Minister in the
work of the Ministry of External Affairs.
(K. Ramiah)
for Cabinet Secretary
To
All Members of the Council of Ministers.
Copy forwarded for inf ormation to the Members
of the Planning Commission.
Copy, forwarded for information to:-
Principal Secretary to the Prime Minister.
Special Secretary to the Prime Minister.
Adviser to the Prime Minis ter (Shri V.s. Tripathi).
Additional Secretary to the Prime Minister.
Joint Secretary to the Prime Minister(Shri Arvind Pande).
Copy forwarded for information to:-
Secretary to the President.
Secretary to the Vice-President.
(K. Ramiah)
Director
2/-
